You see then, that by building your Power on so firm a Foundation, you would have been enabled to dispense Re
wards and Punishments with Justice and Vigour; that you could have displaced the incapable and unworthy, and put into Action those who were most fit to discharge the several Offices of the Commonwealth;
that you could, by Degrees, have checked the Venality and Incapacity of the various Ranks, and thus have given the proper Elasticity and Tone to the several Parts of the Body politic.
